laboratory_examinations.findings: Initial AMH level was 0.20 ng/ml. Gradually increased to 0.50 ng/ml, 0.77 ng/ml, and peaked at 1.26 ng/ml during subsequent treatments.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: AMH levels increased from 0.20 ng/ml to 1.26 ng/ml over the course of treatment, with fluctuations observed: 0.77 ng/ml to 0.51 ng/ml after hCG administration, then increased again with hMG stimulation.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Initial AFC was 0. After treatment, it increased gradually to 2, 4, and peaked at 6.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: AFC increased from 0 to 6 during the treatment cycles.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Initially <1.0 mIU/ml; post-stimulation levels reached 3.4 mIU/ml during tests.
laboratory_examinations.changes_over_time: FSH levels increased as hMG dosage was increased throughout treatment cycles.

laboratory_examinations.findings: Initial estradiol was 28 pg/ml; varied levels observed, but specific future levels not detailed.
Initial prolactin was 4 ng/ml; further measurements not specified.
TSH level was 0.89 mIU/ml; additional data not provided.
